<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-017-090 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 511 060</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Nov 4 1991 n666 p14(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Logic Automation offers first VMEbus model. (introduces SimuBusmodeling software) (Product Announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Goering, Richard.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Logic Automation Inc (Beaverton, OR) introduces the $10,000-plusSimuBus software package for behavioral modeling of the VMEbus.andO;The software enables the simulation of a wide variety offunctional and timing interactions between a proposed VMEbus boarddesign and the host system in IEEE 1014-1987-compliant system,master and slave modes.andP;  SimuBus models include sixexception-driven modules: system, bus master, bus slave, bustimer, bus interrupt handler and bus timer.andP;  The model can controlsuch functions as reads, writes, interrupts, read-modify-writes,block reads and writes, and arbitration.andP;  Logic Automation'sProcessor Control Language (PCL) can be used to program routinesto control these modules, including defining timing delays andgenerating test vectors for the board design and a VMEbusinterface application-specific integrated circuit.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Logic Automation Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   SimuBus (CAD software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionComputer-Aided DesignSoftware PackagesFunctional CapabilitiesVMEbusSimulation of Computer Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>